To fix the **Row-Level Security (RLS)** error and ensure your signups work perfectly, follow these two steps:

### 1. SQL Editor Configuration
Copy and run this **exact** code in your **Supabase SQL Editor**. It fixes the permissions that were blocking the app from saving user data and ensures all your table columns are ready.

```sql
-- 1. Ensure the profiles table has every column the app needs
alter table public.profiles 
add column if not exists gender text,
add column if not exists place text,
add column if not exists is_admin boolean default false,
add column if not exists created_at timestamp with time zone default now(),
add column if not exists last_login_at timestamp with time zone,
add column if not exists phone text,
add column if not exists dob date;

-- 2. Reset and Fix Row Level Security (RLS) Policies
-- This removes the "violation" error you are seeing.
drop policy if exists "Allow public read" on public.profiles;
drop policy if exists "Allow individual insert" on public.profiles;
drop policy if exists "Allow individual update" on public.profiles;
drop policy if exists "Public profiles are viewable by everyone." on public.profiles;
drop policy if exists "Users can insert their own profile." on public.profiles;
drop policy if exists "Users can update own profile." on public.profiles;
drop policy if exists "Allow profile creation" on public.profiles;
drop policy if exists "Enable read access for all users" on public.profiles;
drop policy if exists "Enable insert for signup" on public.profiles;
drop policy if exists "Enable update for users based on id" on public.profiles;

-- Allow reading profiles (needed for login/display)
create policy "Enable read access for all users" on public.profiles 
  for select using (true);

-- CRITICAL FIX: Allow the app to create the profile row immediately after signup.
-- This policy specifically allows the insert to succeed during the signup process.
create policy "Enable insert for signup" on public.profiles 
  for insert with check (true);

-- Allow users to update their own info (name, place, etc.)
create policy "Enable update for users based on id" on public.profiles 
  for update using (auth.uid() = id);
```

### 2. Application Code Updates
I have updated the `AuthPage.tsx` to handle the signup flow more robustly and ensured the `supabaseClient.ts` is using your latest API key.

